High-Yield Summary (Exam-Focused)

1Ô∏è‚É£ AORTA

Parts
	1.	Ascending Aorta
	2.	Arch of Aorta
	3.	Descending Aorta
	‚Ä¢	Thoracic aorta
	‚Ä¢	Abdominal aorta

‚∏ª

Ascending Aorta
	‚Ä¢	Origin: Left ventricle (lower border of 3rd left costal cartilage)
	‚Ä¢	Length: ~2 inches
	‚Ä¢	Location: Inside pericardium
	‚Ä¢	Ends: At sternal angle ‚Üí arch of aorta
	‚Ä¢	Special feature:
	‚Ä¢	3 aortic sinuses (1 anterior, 2 posterior)
	‚Ä¢	Branches:
	‚Ä¢	Right coronary artery
	‚Ä¢	Left coronary artery

‚∏ª

Arch of Aorta
	‚Ä¢	Begins: Right 2nd costal cartilage
	‚Ä¢	Ends: T4 vertebra ‚Üí descending thoracic aorta
	‚Ä¢	Course: Behind manubrium sterni, left of trachea

Branches (üß† VERY EXAM FAVORITE)
	1.	Brachiocephalic trunk
	2.	Left common carotid artery
	3.	Left subclavian artery
	4.	Thyroid ima artery (10%)

Important Relations
	‚Ä¢	Anterior/Left: Left lung, left vagus
	‚Ä¢	Posterior/Right: Trachea, esophagus, left recurrent laryngeal nerve
	‚Ä¢	Inferior:
	‚Ä¢	Left bronchus
	‚Ä¢	Pulmonary trunk bifurcation
	‚Ä¢	Ligamentum arteriosum

‚∏ª

Descending Thoracic Aorta
	‚Ä¢	From: T4
	‚Ä¢	To: T12 (aortic hiatus)

Branches
	‚Ä¢	Posterior intercostal arteries (3‚Äì11)
	‚Ä¢	Subcostal artery (12th)
	‚Ä¢	Bronchial arteries (2)
	‚Ä¢	Esophageal
	‚Ä¢	Pericardial
	‚Ä¢	Mediastinal
	‚Ä¢	Superior phrenic arteries

‚∏ª

Ligamentum Arteriosum
	‚Ä¢	Remnant of ductus arteriosus
	‚Ä¢	Failure to close ‚Üí Patent Ductus Arteriosus (PDA)

PDA clinical pearls
	‚Ä¢	Small: asymptomatic
	‚Ä¢	Large:
	‚Ä¢	Failure to thrive
	‚Ä¢	Recurrent LRTIs
	‚Ä¢	Pulmonary hypertension
	‚Ä¢	Heart failure

‚∏ª

2Ô∏è‚É£ ABDOMINAL AORTA
	‚Ä¢	Begins: T12 (aortic opening of diaphragm)
	‚Ä¢	Ends: L4 ‚Üí right & left common iliac arteries

Relations
	‚Ä¢	Anterior: Pancreas, duodenum (3rd part), left renal vein
	‚Ä¢	Posterior: Lumbar vertebrae
	‚Ä¢	Right: IVC
	‚Ä¢	Left: Left crus, iliopsoas

Branches (üß† CLASSIC EXAM TABLE)

Ventral
	‚Ä¢	Celiac trunk
	‚Ä¢	SMA
	‚Ä¢	IMA

Lateral
	‚Ä¢	Inferior phrenic (2)
	‚Ä¢	Renal (2)
	‚Ä¢	Middle suprarenal (2)
	‚Ä¢	Gonadal (2)

Dorsal
	‚Ä¢	Lumbar arteries (4 pairs)
	‚Ä¢	Median sacral

Terminal
	‚Ä¢	Common iliac arteries (2)

‚∏ª

3Ô∏è‚É£ VEINS OF THORAX

Superior Vena Cava (SVC)
	‚Ä¢	Formed by: Union of brachiocephalic veins
	‚Ä¢	Drains: Head, neck, upper limbs
	‚Ä¢	Terminates: Right atrium (Rt 3rd costal cartilage)

Tributaries
	‚Ä¢	Azygos vein (T4)
	‚Ä¢	Mediastinal veins
	‚Ä¢	Pericardial veins

‚∏ª

Inferior Vena Cava (IVC)
	‚Ä¢	Formed: L5 (common iliac veins)
	‚Ä¢	Course: Right of abdominal aorta
	‚Ä¢	Terminates: Right atrium (via diaphragm at T8)

Tributaries
	‚Ä¢	Lumbar veins
	‚Ä¢	Renal veins
	‚Ä¢	Hepatic veins
	‚Ä¢	Right gonadal vein
	‚Ä¢	Right suprarenal vein

‚∏ª

4Ô∏è‚É£ ARTERIES OF HEAD & NECK

Common Carotid Artery
	‚Ä¢	Right: From brachiocephalic trunk
	‚Ä¢	Left: From arch of aorta
	‚Ä¢	Termination: C3‚ÄìC4 ‚Üí Internal & External carotid

‚∏ª

External Carotid Artery
	‚Ä¢	Ends: Parotid gland ‚Üí superficial temporal + maxillary

Branches (Mnemonic: Some Angry Lady Figured Out PMS)
	‚Ä¢	Anterior:
	‚Ä¢	Superior thyroid
	‚Ä¢	Lingual
	‚Ä¢	Facial
	‚Ä¢	Medial: Ascending pharyngeal
	‚Ä¢	Posterior:
	‚Ä¢	Occipital
	‚Ä¢	Posterior auricular
	‚Ä¢	Terminal:
	‚Ä¢	Maxillary
	‚Ä¢	Superficial temporal

‚∏ª

Maxillary Artery
	‚Ä¢	Divided into 3 parts (by lateral pterygoid)

Key branch: Middle meningeal artery

‚∏ª

Subclavian Artery
	‚Ä¢	Right: From brachiocephalic trunk
	‚Ä¢	Left: From arch of aorta
	‚Ä¢	Ends: Outer border of 1st rib ‚Üí axillary artery

Divided into 3 parts by scalenus anterior

Main branches
	‚Ä¢	Vertebral
	‚Ä¢	Internal thoracic
	‚Ä¢	Thyrocervical trunk
	‚Ä¢	Costocervical trunk

‚∏ª

5Ô∏è‚É£ VEINS OF HEAD & NECK

Internal Jugular Vein
	‚Ä¢	Begins: Jugular foramen
	‚Ä¢	Ends: Joins subclavian ‚Üí brachiocephalic vein
	‚Ä¢	Course: In carotid sheath

Tributaries
	‚Ä¢	Inferior petrosal sinus
	‚Ä¢	Common facial vein
	‚Ä¢	Superior & middle thyroid veins

‚∏ª

‚≠ê EXAM PEARLS (SAVE THESE)
	‚Ä¢	Left recurrent laryngeal nerve loops under arch of aorta
	‚Ä¢	PDA = failure of ductus arteriosus closure
	‚Ä¢	Aortic bifurcation = L4
	‚Ä¢	IVC passes diaphragm at T8
	‚Ä¢	Esophagus relation = posterior to arch
	‚Ä¢	Middle meningeal artery ‚Üí epidural hematoma
	‚Ä¢	Carotid bifurcation at C3‚ÄìC4

